---
<BaseLayout title="Codebolt — AI Engine for Agent-Native Software" navbarVariant="transparent" site={site} navigation={navigation}>
  <Hero
    heading="The Self-Improving, Hyper-Scaling AI Agent Engine"
    subheading="Build, run, and ship agent-native software."
  />
  <StartTabs
    eyebrow="Use Codebolt where you work"
    media={{"alt":"Codebolt product demo","placeholder":"Product GIF space"}}
    tabs={[{"label":"CLI","body":"Install globally with npm. Run in your terminal. Use a built-in agent or write your own — full SDK access, any LLM provider.","code":"npm i -g codebolt","primary":{"label":"Install Guide","href":"/products/cli"},"more":{"label":"View CLI","href":"/products/cli"}},{"label":"Editor","body":"Polished desktop IDE with the engine running locally. Monaco editor, agent workspace, plugin panel. Available for macOS, Windows, and Linux.","primary":{"label":"Download Editor","href":"/download"},"more":{"label":"View Editor","href":"/products/editor"}},{"label":"Cloud","body":"Hosted engine in your browser. No install. Spawn workspaces, run agents on managed sandboxes, share state with your team.","primary":{"label":"Open Cloud","href":"https://cloud.codebolt.ai"},"more":{"label":"View Cloud","href":"/products/cloud"}}]}
  />
  <HighlightBanner
    tone="accent"
    content={`Start like Claude Code. Scale like nothing else exists. <span class="text-primary">One engine. Every scale.</span>
`}
  />
  <StatGrid
    tone="muted"
    columns={3}
    stats={[{"label":"SDK Modules","value":"63+"},{"label":"LLM Providers","value":"17+"},{"label":"Communication Channels","value":"3"},{"label":"Environments","value":"Unlimited"}]}
  />
  <CenteredText
    variant="thesis"
    text="Claude Code is an agent. OpenClaw is an assistant. Cursor is an editor. Codebolt is the engine that can become any of them — and scale beyond all of them."
  />
  <IconGrid
    tone="muted"
    kicker="WHAT IS AGENT-NATIVE SOFTWARE"
    title="Software that runs itself, improves itself,
distributes itself, and composes with other software like it.
"
    description="Agent-native software has properties traditional software doesn't. Codebolt is the engine that makes them possible."
    columns={5}
    features={[{"icon":"zap","title":"Runs itself","description":"Autonomous loops, hooks, schedules, webhooks. The agent stays in motion without you driving it. You don't have to be in the loop for work to happen."},{"icon":"git-branch","title":"Improves itself","description":"Define what good looks like with eval tasks. The optimizer iterates on prompts, tools, and configs across runs. Your agents get measurably better with use, not worse."},{"icon":"layers","title":"Distributes itself","description":"Lives where customers already are — Slack, Telegram, Discord, email, web. The Routing Gateway carries the same agent to every surface, no glue code."},{"icon":"cpu","title":"Composes","description":"Agents call agents. Multi-agent by default. Stigmergy, deliberation councils, review-merge — coordination is built in, not bolted on."}]}
  />
  <ProgressionStrip
    kicker="THE SCALE SPECTRUM"
    heading="One Engine. Every Scale."
    description="The same engine powers every level. Start anywhere. Scale without rebuilding."
    steps={[{"label":"CLI","description":"A coding agent in your terminal. One agent, full SDK.","reference":"Like Claude Code"},{"label":"Editor","description":"Desktop editor with agent workspace and plugin panel.","reference":"Like Cursor"},{"label":"24/7 Agent","description":"Always-on agent with persistent memory and plugin integrations.","reference":"Like OpenClaw / Hermes"},{"label":"Orchestration","description":"50-100+ agents coordinated across environments.","reference":"Beyond any single tool"},{"label":"Autonomous Company","description":"Business domains as plugins. Agents coordinate across all of them.","reference":"Like Paperclip, but built-in"}]}
  />
  <ShowcaseStrip
    kicker="ENGINE · SURFACES"
    heading="One engine. Every surface."
    subtitle="Same engine, same SDK, same plugins — different interface for different needs."
    columns={4}
    items={[{"title":"CLI","description":"Terminal client. Like Claude Code, but with custom agents and a growth path to multi-agent.","href":"/products/cli","visual":"$ codebolt\n$ codebolt --agent my-agent\n$ codebolt --server\n$ codebolt --prompt \"...\"\n"},{"title":"Editor","description":"Desktop editor with Monaco, agent workspace, and plugin panel. Not a fork.","href":"/products/editor","visual":"┌──────────┬──────────┐\n│ Editor   │ Agents   │\n├──────────┴──────────┤\n│ Terminal │ Plugins  │\n└─────────────────────┘\n"},{"title":"24/7 Autonomous Agent","description":"Always-on agent with persistent memory and plugin integrations. Reaches your customers wherever they are.","href":"/products/autonomous-agent","visual":"Always-on engine\n├─ Memory (3-tier)\n├─ Plugins (external)\n├─ Hooks (proactive)\n└─ Any LLM provider\n"},{"title":"Cloud","description":"Hosted engine with a browser portal. Sandbox runs, shared workspaces, no install.","href":"/products/cloud","visual":"cloud.codebolt.ai\n├─ Browser portal\n├─ Managed sandboxes\n├─ Shared workspaces\n└─ Same engine inside\n"}]}
  />
  <SdkCallout
    kicker="BUILD YOUR OWN SURFACE"
    heading="SDK for products that need the engine inside."
    description="Use the Agent SDK, Plugin SDK, and Client SDK to embed Codebolt in your own product, ship agent-native apps, or run the engine headless on your infrastructure."
    features={["Agent SDK","Plugin SDK","Client SDK","Self-hosted engine"]}
    cta={{"label":"Explore the SDK","href":"/products/sdk"}}
  />
  <FeatureShowcase
    kicker="THE ENGINE"
    heading="The pillars of the engine"
    subtitle="Extensible at every layer. Self-improving by design. Moldable at the surface."
    heroFeatures={[{"title":"System Extensibility","description":"Three SDKs. Agent SDK (63+ modules), Plugin SDK (3 channels), Client SDK (72 REST + 33 WS). The system is open at every layer.","href":"/engine/system-extensibility","tag":"EXTEND THE SYSTEM","visual":"Agent SDK → codeboltjs (63+ modules)\nPlugin SDK → WS + Mux + HTTP\nClient SDK → 72 REST + 33 WS\nAll open. All extensible.\n"},{"title":"Agent Extensibility","description":"Remix agents (no-code YAML), Flow agents (visual graph), Custom agents (full code). 675+ skills across 72 domains. Role-specific LLM configs.","href":"/engine/agent-extensibility","tag":"EXTEND ANY AGENT","visual":"Remix: YAML + Markdown (no code)\nFlow:  Visual graph editor\nCustom: Full SDK access (code)\nSkills: 675+ across 72 domains\n"},{"title":"Self-Improving by Design","description":"Define what good looks like with eval tasks. The optimizer iterates on prompts, tools, and configs across runs. Your agents get measurably better with use, not worse.","tag":"EVAL · OPTIMIZE","visual":"eval task → score\n  ↓\noptimizer → tweak prompt/tools\n  ↓\nre-run → new score\n  ↓\nkeep winners. Forever loop.\n"}]}
    compactFeatures={[{"title":"Dynamic Interface Generation","description":"Panels and plugins compose into the surface your customers see. Ship a vertical IDE, a domain-specific UI, or a SaaS — assembled from the engine's parts.","tag":"MOLDABLE"},{"title":"Multi-Agent Scaling","description":"Sub-agents, parallel execution, stigmergy coordination, pheromone ownership, deliberation councils, auto review & merge — within one environment.","href":"/engine/multi-agent","tag":"COORDINATION"},{"title":"Multi-Environment Scaling","description":"Proxy execution chains environments. Env A → B → C. Any topology. Git bundle state transfer.","href":"/engine/multi-environment","tag":"ACROSS MACHINES"},{"title":"Narrative Engine","description":"Rust-based flight recorder. Shadow git snapshots. Per-thread history. Deterministic replay.","tag":"RUST"},{"title":"Guardrails","description":"Policy engine with LLM risk classification. Per-role, per-environment, per-phase. Allow, deny, escalate.","tag":"GOVERNANCE"},{"title":"Three-Tier Memory","description":"Episodic + Persistent + Context Assembly Engine. Token budgets. Agents know what to remember.","tag":"MEMORY"}]}
  />
  <QuoteBlock
    variant="muted"
    align="center"
    quote="The same engine that powers a simple coding CLI also powers a 100-agent autonomous company. Everything you build — agents, plugins, memory, workflows — carries forward as you scale."
    attribution="Codebolt Engineering"
  />
  <BentoGrid
    kicker="ABOUT THE ENGINE"
    heading="Built different. Scales different."
    description="An advanced agent execution engine — from one agent to autonomous companies."
    columns={3}
    items={[{"title":"63+ SDK Modules","description":"Filesystem, git, browser, terminal, LLM, vector DB, memory, knowledge graph, code search, and more.","tag":"AGENT SDK","span":1,"visual":"codebolt.fs    codebolt.git\ncodebolt.llm   codebolt.browser\ncodebolt.terminal  codebolt.vectordb\ncodebolt.memory  codebolt.agent\n... 55 more modules\n"},{"title":"3 Communication Channels","description":"Agent channel for work. Plugin channel for extensions. Client channel for interfaces. Each serves a distinct purpose.","tag":"ARCHITECTURE","span":2,"visual":"Agent Ch.  ──→ codeboltjs SDK ──→ 63+ modules\nPlugin Ch. ──→ WS + Mux + HTTP ──→ runs inside engine\nClient Ch. ──→ 72 REST + 33 WS ──→ build any interface\n"},{"title":"17+ LLM Providers","description":"OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Mistral, Groq, DeepSeek, Ollama, LM Studio. Per-agent, per-task model selection.","tag":"MODEL AGNOSTIC","span":1},{"title":"Multi-Environment","description":"Local, Docker, cloud, hierarchical. Proxy execution chains them together. Git bundles transfer state.","tag":"INFRASTRUCTURE","span":1,"visual":"local → Docker → cloud\n↕ proxy execution\nAny topology. Any scale.\n"},{"title":"Stigmergy + Deliberation","description":"Bio-inspired coordination. Pheromone task ownership. Agent deliberation councils. Review & merge without GitHub PR bottleneck.","tag":"COORDINATION","span":1,"visual":"Agents → shared state\nPheromones → ownership\nDeliberation → consensus\nAuto-merge → no bottleneck\n"}]}
  />
  <ComparisonColumns
    problem={{"heading":"Other tools","items":["Claude Code — great CLI agent, but you can't customize the loop or scale beyond one agent","Cursor — great IDE, but agents are fixed and there's no plugin system","OpenClaw — great personal agent, but no multi-agent coordination or enterprise scaling","LangChain/CrewAI — agent frameworks, but no execution environment","Each tool is one thing. If you outgrow it, you start over."]}}
    solution={{"heading":"Codebolt","items":["One engine that starts as a CLI and scales to orchestrate 100+ agents","Full control over the agentic loop — write agents in code, not prompts","Plugin system with 3 communication channels — plugins run inside the platform","Multi-environment scaling across local, Docker, cloud, and hierarchical setups","Everything carries forward. Agents, plugins, memory, workflows — nothing gets rebuilt."]}}
  />
  <ComparisonTable
    kicker="COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE"
    heading="How Codebolt compares"
    description="Every tool does one thing. Codebolt is the engine that does all of them."
    highlightColumn={1}
    columns={["Capability","Codebolt","Claude Code","OpenClaw","Paperclip","Hermes","Letta","Cursor"]}
    rows={[{"label":"What it is","values":["Agent engine (CLI → autonomous company)","CLI coding agent","Personal AI assistant","Company orchestrator (manages agents, doesn't run them)","Self-improving agent framework","Stateful agent platform","AI-enhanced IDE"]},{"label":"Runs agents","values":["Yes — custom agents via 63-module SDK","Built-in only","Built-in only","No — orchestrates external agents","Yes — function-calling","Yes — stateful agents","Built-in only"]},{"label":"Multi-agent orchestration","values":["Yes — stigmergy, deliberation, 100+ agents","No","No","Yes — org charts, roles, budgets","No","Limited","No"]},{"label":"Scales to","values":["1 to 100+ agents, multi-environment","1 agent","1 agent","Depends on agents you bring","1 agent (subagents)","1-10 agents","1 agent"]},{"label":"Memory system","values":["3-tier (episodic, persistent, context assembly)","Session only","Persistent","None","Persistent + learning loop","Persistent (core feature)","Session only"]},{"label":"Plugin system","values":["Yes — 3 channels (WS, Mux, HTTP)","Skills (limited)","Skills/integrations","Agent adapters","Skills (agentskills.io)","No","VS Code extensions"]},{"label":"Surfaces","values":["CLI + Editor + TUI + Cloud + headless","CLI + IDE extensions","Web + chat apps","Web dashboard","CLI + chat apps","CLI + API","IDE only"]},{"label":"Self-improving","values":["Yes — memory compounds, context optimizes","No","Yes — writes own skills","No","Yes — learning loop","Yes — background subagents","No"]}]}
  />
  <IconGrid
    tone="muted"
    kicker="ENGINE CAPABILITIES"
    title="What makes the engine powerful
63+ modules. 3 channels. Unlimited scale.
"
    description="Every capability is available at every scale — from CLI to autonomous company."
    columns={3}
    features={[{"icon":"layers","title":"63+ SDK Modules","description":"Filesystem, git, browser, terminal, LLM, vector DB, memory, knowledge graph, code search, and more."},{"icon":"cpu","title":"3 Communication Channels","description":"Agent channel (codeboltjs), Plugin channel (WS + HTTP), Client channel (UI/TUI/Web). Each serves a purpose."},{"icon":"git-branch","title":"Multi-Environment","description":"Local, Docker, cloud, hierarchical. State transfer via git bundles. Heartbeat monitoring. Full lifecycle management."},{"icon":"shield","title":"Guardrails & Governance","description":"Policy engine with LLM risk classification. Per-agent, per-environment, per-phase scoping. Allow, deny, or escalate."},{"icon":"code","title":"17+ LLM Providers","description":"OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Mistral, Groq, DeepSeek, Ollama, LM Studio. Per-agent, per-task model selection."},{"icon":"zap","title":"Built-in Review & Merge","description":"Agents review each other's work. Conflict detection. Pheromone coordination. No GitHub PR bottleneck."}]}
  />
  <ConnectivityGrid
    kicker="REACH"
    heading="Reachable from everywhere"
    description="The engine connects to your entire workflow through its plugin system. Native interfaces plus anything plugins can reach."
    columns={4}
    items={[{"label":"Terminal / CLI","category":"interface"},{"label":"Desktop IDE","category":"interface"},{"label":"Web UI","category":"interface"},{"label":"TUI","category":"interface"},{"label":"WhatsApp","category":"messaging"},{"label":"Telegram","category":"messaging"},{"label":"Slack","category":"messaging"},{"label":"Discord","category":"messaging"},{"label":"Email","category":"communication"},{"label":"Webhooks","category":"automation"},{"label":"CI/CD Pipelines","category":"automation"},{"label":"REST API","category":"automation"}]}
  />
  <QuoteBlock
    variant="muted"
    align="center"
    quote="The engine doesn't just run agents — it learns. Three-tier memory compounds knowledge across sessions. Skills improve through use. Context assembly optimizes what each agent sees. The longer you run Codebolt, the smarter it gets."
    attribution="Codebolt Engineering"
  />
  <CardGrid
    heading="The Progression"
    cards={[{"title":"Day 1 — CLI in your terminal","body":"Install Codebolt. Run it in your terminal. Use a built-in agent or bring your own. Like Claude Code but with any model, full SDK access, and room to grow.","visual":"$ npm i -g codebolt\n$ codebolt\n→ Start with the engine\n"},{"title":"Week 2 — Custom Agents","body":"Write your first agent in 10 lines of JavaScript. Full access to 63+ SDK modules. Your logic, your tools, your rules. No other tool gives you this for free.","visual":"import { codebolt } from 'codeboltjs';\ncodebolt.onMessage(async (msg) => {\n  // your agent, your logic\n});\n"},{"title":"Month 2 — Editor + Plugins","body":"Switch to the desktop Editor. Install plugins that connect to GitHub, Jira, Slack. Build custom plugins. Multiple agents coordinating on your codebase.","visual":"Editor + Monaco\nPlugins: CI/CD, review, deploy\n3+ agents coordinating\n"},{"title":"Month 6 — 24/7 Autonomous Agent","body":"Your agent runs always-on. Persistent memory. Proactive scheduling. Plugin integrations handle email, calendar, monitoring. Like OpenClaw, but on an engine that scales.","visual":"Always-on engine\nMemory persists across sessions\nPlugins handle the world\n"},{"title":"Year 1 — Orchestration","body":"50+ agents across Docker and cloud environments. Stigmergy coordination. Deliberation councils. Automatic review and merge. Drift tracking. Your infrastructure, not your bottleneck.","visual":"50+ agents → 5 environments\nAuto review & merge\nDrift tracking + guardrails\n"},{"title":"Year 2 — Autonomous Company","body":"Applications run as plugins inside the engine. Each handles a domain — engineering, testing, deployment, monitoring. Agents coordinate across all of them. You direct the vision.","visual":"Plugin: Engineering\nPlugin: QA & Testing\nPlugin: Deployment\nPlugin: Monitoring\nAll autonomous. You direct.\n"}]}
  />
  <PersonaGrid
    personas={[{"label":"Solo Developers","body":"Start with the CLI. Use one agent. Write custom agents when you're ready. More power than any free coding tool — because you control the agent, not just the prompt."},{"label":"Teams Scaling AI","body":"When two agents edit the same repo, the platform resolves conflicts. Coordination, drift tracking, and multi-environment management — so you focus on the product."},{"label":"AI Startup Founders","body":"Build your company on the engine. Applications run as plugins — no separate agent instances needed. Scale across environments as you grow."},{"label":"Enterprise & Production","body":"Governance, audit trails, deterministic replay, and guardrails. Every agent decision is traceable. Every change is attributable. Deploy agents in production with confidence."},{"label":"Platform Engineers","body":"Run headless in CI/CD. Spawn Docker environments. Transfer state between them. Monitor with real-time events. The engine was built for infrastructure people."},{"label":"AI Researchers","body":"Stigmergy-based coordination. Pheromone systems. Narrative versioning. Agent deliberation councils. Research-grounded architecture with published foundations."}]}
  />
  <CtaBlock
    heading="One engine. Start simple. Scale without limits."
    buttons={[{"label":"Get Started","href":"/pricing","variant":"primary"},{"label":"Explore the Engine","href":"/engine","variant":"secondary"}]}
  />
</BaseLayout>
